# Thunderbird Extension APIs

## Experiment APIs

This extension uses a custom WebExtension Experiment API defined in [headerApi.js](mdc:src/api/headerApi.js) and [headerApi.json](mdc:src/api/headerApi.json).

### Manifest Registration

```json
"experiment_apis": {
  "headerApi": {
    "schema": "api/headerApi.json",
    "parent": {
      "scopes": ["addon_parent"],
      "paths": [["headerApi"]],
      "script": "api/headerApi.js"
    }
  }
}
```

### API Scope

Experiment APIs run in privileged context with access to:

- `Services` (Firefox/Thunderbird internal services)
- `ChromeUtils` (low-level utilities)
- Direct DOM manipulation of mail UI
- XPCOM components

## HeaderAPI Implementation

### Main Functions

#### `browser.headerApi.pictureHeaders(tabId, payloadJson)`

Renders avatars in message headers and inbox list.

#### `browser.headerApi.pictureHeadersConversation(tabId, payloadJson)`

Renders avatars in Thunderbird Conversations view.

### Version Detection in Experiment API

```javascript
function getThunderbirdVersion() {
  try {
    const appInfo = Services.appinfo;
    const version = appInfo.version;
    return parseInt(version.split(".")[0], 10);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Error getting Thunderbird version:", error);
    return 145; // Safe default
  }
}
```

### Installation Functions

#### `installOnRow(row, url, tbVersion)`

Installs avatar on inbox list row:

- TB 145+: Creates canvas element
- TB < 145: Creates img element
- Handles both avatar images and initials

#### `installOnMessageHeader(header, url, tbVersion)`

Installs avatar in message header:

- Located via `.recipient-avatar` selector
- Size: 34x34px
- Uses namespace for img elements in older versions

#### `installConversation(conversation, data, win, tbVersion)`

Installs avatars in conversation view:

- Popups: `.authorPicture` (48x48px)
- Messages: `.contactInitials` or `.auto-profile-picture` (32x32px)

### Canvas Rendering (TB 145+)

```javascript
async function drawDataUrlToCanvas(dataUrl, canvas, width, height, win) {
  const parts = dataUrl.split(",");
  const mimeMatch = parts[0].match(/:(.*?);/);
  const mimeType = mimeMatch ? mimeMatch[1] : "image/png";

  const binaryString = win.atob(parts[1]);
  const bytes = new Uint8Array(binaryString.length);
  for (let i = 0; i < binaryString.length; i++) {
    bytes[i] = binaryString.charCodeAt(i);
  }

  const blob = new Blob([bytes], { type: mimeType });
  const imageBitmap = await win.createImageBitmap(blob);

  const ctx = canvas.getContext("2d");
  ctx.drawImage(imageBitmap, 0, 0, width, height);
}
```

## Standard WebExtension APIs

### Browser Storage API

Used for persistent settings and cache:

```javascript
// Save to storage
await browser.storage.local.set({ key: value });

// Read from storage
const result = await browser.storage.local.get(key);
const value = result[key];

// Remove from storage
await browser.storage.local.remove(key);
```

### Messages API

Read email messages:

```javascript
// Get full message
const full = await browser.messages.getFull(messageId);

// List messages
const messages = await browser.messages.list(folder);

// Get message details
const message = await browser.messages.get(messageId);
```

### Accounts API

Access Thunderbird accounts:

```javascript
// List all accounts
const accounts = await browser.accounts.list();

// Get specific account
const account = await browser.accounts.get(accountId);
```

### Contacts/Address Books API

Manage contacts:

```javascript
// List address books
const addressBooks = await browser.addressBooks.list();

// Get contacts
const contacts = await browser.contacts.list(addressBookId);

// Update contact with photo
await browser.contacts.update(contactId, {
  photoDataUrl: dataUrl,
});
```

### Runtime API

```javascript
// Get browser info (for version detection)
const info = await browser.runtime.getBrowserInfo();

// Send messages between scripts
browser.runtime.sendMessage({ type: "update", data: payload });

// Listen for messages
browser.runtime.onMessage.addListener((message) => {
  // Handle message
});
```

## Permissions Required

From [manifest.json](mdc:src/manifest.json):

```json
"permissions": [
  "messagesRead",   // Read email messages
  "accountsRead",   // Read account information
  "storage",        // Local storage access
  "addressBooks",   // Contact management
  "<all_urls>"      // Network requests to any domain
]
```

## Background Script

[background.js](mdc:src/background.js) is the main entry point:

- Initializes all services
- Handles message passing
- Coordinates avatar fetching
- Manages settings updates

### Service Initialization Pattern

```javascript
// Create services
const cache = new CacheStorage();
const settingsManager = new SettingsManager(cache);
const avatarService = new AvatarService();
const mailService = new MailService(avatarService);

// Load settings
let inboxListEnabled = await settingsManager.getInboxListEnabled();
```

## Event Handling

### Tab Events

```javascript
browser.tabs.onUpdated.addListener(async (tabId, changeInfo, tab) => {
  if (changeInfo.status === "complete") {
    // Tab loaded, install avatars
  }
});
```

### Display Events

```javascript
browser.headerApi.onDisplayed.addListener(async (result) => {
  const tab = result.tab;
  // Handle avatar display
});
```

## CSP Compliance

### Content Security Policy

Extension pages must comply with CSP:

- No inline scripts
- No `eval()` or `new Function()`
- No inline event handlers
- TB 145+: No data URLs in img src (use canvas instead)

### Manifest CSP (if needed)

```json
"content_security_policy": "default-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data:;"
```

## Debugging

### Console Access

- Background script console: Tools → Developer Tools → Browser Console
- Experiment API: Check Browser Console (privileged context)
- Options page: Right-click → Inspect Element

### Logging Best Practices

```javascript
// Include context in logs
console.log("Installing avatar for", email, "in tab", tabId);

// Log errors with full context
console.error("Failed to fetch avatar:", {
  author: author.getAuthor(),
  provider: provider.name,
  error: error.message,
});
```
